&lt;/h1>&lt;h2 id="-lorentzian-classification-machine-learning-driven-tradingview-indicator--nadaraya-watson-envelope--voss-predictor-indicator"># Lorentzian Classification Machine Learning Driven TradingView Indicator + Nadaraya Watson Envelope + Voss Predictor Indicator
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://i.imgur.com/Pcf7S1g.png"
loading="lazy"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://i.imgur.com/T3xVF9N.png"
loading="lazy"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://i.imgur.com/mVqtyZf.png"
loading="lazy"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>Use &lt;strong>Regime Filter&lt;/strong> to increase or decrease calls.&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>Regime Filter negative → More calls.&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>Regime Filter positive → Less calls, more rigorous.&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>Use &lt;strong>ADX Filter&lt;/strong> for the same.&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>Don’t have both (regime &amp;amp; ADX) together.&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>EMA, SMA for contra trends. Don’t do contra trends for 10 min 12 min&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>Use Kernel settings to increase hit rate. Find patterns like head &amp;amp; shoulder.&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>“Relative weight” to increase win rate in a specific time interval.&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>Use Nadaria Whatson indicator ( from same author ) to confirm bearish or bullish.
&lt;img src="https://i.imgur.com/3XKR5Nm.png"
loading="lazy"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
